title: Topology Generated by a Basis
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

For a [[Basis]] $$\mathcal{B}$$, the ''topology generated by the basis'' is constructed by defining $$\mathcal{T}$$ to be the [[Empty Set]] and all [[Union]]s of elements of $$\mathcal{B}$$.